A command-line based Task and Data Manager built using Python, designed to demonstrate core programming concepts such as object-oriented programming (OOP), file handling, and user authentication. The application allows users to sign up, log in, and manage their data efficiently through a structured CLI interface.

The system uses CSV files for persistent storage, enabling data to be saved and retrieved across sessions. It includes features like user management, input validation, and error handling, making it a practical example of real-world Python application design.

This project is ideal for showcasing proficiency in Python fundamentals aligned with PCAP and PCEP certification topics, including classes, functions, control flow, and modular programming.